<DocsLayout title="Session Metrics & Savings Dashboard" description="Track token savings with ctx_metrics (per session), lean-ctx gain (CLI), and lean-ctx dashboard (web UI).">
  <p>
    lean-ctx tracks token savings at three levels:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Per-session</strong> via the <code>ctx_metrics</code> MCP tool (in-editor)</li>
    <li><strong>Lifetime CLI</strong> via <code>lean-ctx gain</code> (terminal)</li>
    <li><strong>Web Dashboard</strong> via <code>lean-ctx dashboard</code> (browser)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Both MCP tool calls and shell hook invocations are tracked in <code>~/.lean-ctx/stats.json</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>lean-ctx dashboard (Web UI)</h2>
  <p>
    Opens an interactive web dashboard at <code>http://localhost:3333</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code>lean-ctx dashboard
lean-ctx dashboard --port=8080</code></pre>
  <p>The dashboard includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>5 KPI cards</strong> — Tokens Saved, Savings Rate, Total Commands, Days Active, Cost Saved</li>
    <li><strong>5 interactive charts</strong> — Cumulative savings (area), daily rate (line), daily activity (stacked bar), top commands (horizontal bar), command distribution (doughnut)</li>
    <li><strong>MCP vs Shell Hook breakdown</strong> — separate stats and badges for MCP tools (ctx_read etc.) and shell hook commands (git, npm etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Command table</strong> — all commands with count, input/output tokens, savings rate, and visual compression bars</li>
    <li><strong>Daily history</strong> — last 30 days with activity bars</li>
  </ul>

